This simple Java program calculates the sum of the first n natural numbers (including 0).
It takes an integer input n from the user and uses a for loop to compute the sum from 0 to n


import java.util.*;
class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc=new Scanner (System.in);
        int n=sc.nextInt();
        int sum=0;
        for(int i=0;i<n+1;i++){
            sum=sum+i;
        }
        System.out.println(sum);
        
    }
    
}


Example
5
Output:
15

Explanation: 0 + 1 + 2 + 3 + 4 + 5 = 15
